 Variables + Data Types

This is where real programming starts. If you don’t understand this properly, everything later (arrays, OOP, DSA) will confuse you.

1. What is a Variable?

A variable is just a container that stores data.

Example 1

int age = 20;

Example 2

String name = "Vishnu";

Here:

age stores a number
name stores text
2. Data Types in Java

Java is strictly typed. You must define the type before storing data.

Main types:
Type	Meaning	Example
int	integer	10, 100
double	decimal	10.5
char	single character	'A'
String	text	"Hello"
boolean	true/false	true
3. Examples

Example 1

int a = 10;
double b = 5.5;

System.out.println(a);
System.out.println(b);

Example 2

char grade = 'A';
boolean isPass = true;

System.out.println(grade);
System.out.println(isPass);
4. Combining Variables

Example 1

int a = 10;
int b = 20;

System.out.println(a + b);

Example 2

String name = "Vishnu";
int age = 20;

System.out.println("Name: " + name);
System.out.println("Age: " + age);
5. Important Mistakes Beginners Make

Mistake 1 — Forgetting quotes

String name = Vishnu;   // WRONG

Correct

String name = "Vishnu";

Mistake 2 — Using wrong type

int price = 10.5;   // WRONG

Correct

double price = 10.5;
